messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants the Den Lamp to turn on to 75% brightness.
2. The trigger is a physical turn on of the Hall-End I3 Paddle, which is a COC event (command sent by device).
3. The Hall-End I3 Paddle sends a Fast On (DFON) command when physically turned on.
4. The action is to send the On command (DON) to Den Lamp with parameter 75% (On Level).

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Den Lamp when Hall-End I3 Paddle physically turned on",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Hall-End I3 Paddle",
        "coc": "DFON",
        "parameters": []
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "Den Lamp",
      "command": "On",
      "parameters": [
        { "name": "On Level", "value": 75, "uom": "percent", "precision": 1 }
      ]
    }
  }
}
